Write tests for the code you just wrote. Follow these steps:
1. First, examine existing tests in the project to understand testing conventions
2. Identify the testing framework used (pytest, unittest, jest, etc.)
3. Create tests in the appropriate location following project structure
4. Write tests for the happy path - normal expected behavior
5. Write tests for edge cases: empty inputs, null values, boundary conditions
6. Write tests for error conditions - ensure errors are raised appropriately
7. Use descriptive test names that explain what is being tested
8. Each test should test ONE thing - keep tests focused and independent
9. Use appropriate fixtures or setup/teardown if needed
10. Run the tests to verify they pass
11. Ensure tests actually test the new code, not just trivial assertions
